import React, {useEffect, useState} from 'react'; import api from '../services/api'; import { Container, Grid, Typography, Table, TableHead, TableRow, TableCell, TableBody } from '@mui/material'; import DashboardCard from '../components/DashboardCard'; export default function Dashboard(){ const [health, setHealth] = useState('...'); const [students, setStudents] = useState([]); const [attendance, setAttendance] = useState([]); useEffect(()=>{ api.get('/api/v1/health') .then(r=>setHealth(r.data.status)) .catch(()=>setHealth('unreachable')) api.get('/api/v1/students') .then(r=> setStudents(r.data || [])) .catch(()=> setStudents([])) api.get('/api/v1/attendance') .then(r=> setAttendance(r.data || [])) .catch(()=> setAttendance([])) },[]) const studentsCount = Array.isArray(students) ? students.length : '--'; let attendancePct = '--'; if(Array.isArray(attendance) && studentsCount && studentsCount > 0){ attendancePct = Math.round((attendance.length / Math.max(1, studentsCount)) * 100) + '%'; } return ( Dashboard {/* Larger area with raw data preview */} Recent attendance
Student Method Location Timestamp {attendance.slice(0,10).map(a => ( {a.student_id} {a.method} {a.location} {new Date(a.timestamp).toLocaleString()} ))}
Quick actions

• Use the Students page to view full list.

• Use Attendance for details and exports.

 ) }
